from Soup: 28 In addition, we applied the model to the data of Broussely et al., 36 predicting capacity fade at 15°C for 14.5 months using data at 30–60°C for 6 months. In this case, the second term in equation 4 was statistically indistinguishable from zero, meaning that a simple t 1/2 capacity fade model would give the same result. It is possible that the second term cannot be distinguished in this case because capacity loss was not measured directly, as in Smith et al., 29 but inferred from measured capacity. Figure 8 compares the prediction with experimental data.
