from Soup: 40 Although for most choices of f(s) it is not possible to find an analytic formula for Q(t) , we can make progress in the simple case fs=st0 , in the limit k →∞ (which experiments 28 suggest is reasonable: see above). Under these conditions, where Q 0 is the initial capacity. We see that the long-term linear fade has the same prefactor as the t 1/2 fade of the stable case, except for the dimensionally-required 1 / (2 t 0 1/2 ). This long-term behavior is not influenced by the assumption k →∞.
